getExtensionClassesForScopes.description:
Sirius is a tool for program and project management which enables multiple parallel or subsequent deliveries in one program.

It also allows the delivery of an On-Premise and Cloud product in one mixed delivery (working on a combined set of program tasks), if they have the same delivery date.
Smart Program Management

Sirius contains:
- details of programs and their deliveries (example: "Release type")
- role staffing (example: Who is the Program Lead?)
- a Release Planner with planning milestones (e.g. RTC)

getExtensionClassesForScopes.name: mend
getExtensionClassesForScopes.description:
The step Open Source Lifecycle Manager from Whitesource (referred to as only "Whitesource" going forward) is a SaaS solution that can be integrated with your build process and which identify used Open Source Software (OSS), audits your open source licenses, as well as security vulnerabilities, every time you run your build. This build integration is done via plugins. Those plugins integrate with your build process and calculate the digital signature for all your components without ever scanning your source code. It then sends the information about your open source components (and only that) to the WhiteSource server which matches all components and dependencies to the WhiteSource knowledge base. An immediate up-to-date report is generated, identifying all components and issues detected. WhiteSource can be used as a step for intellectual property (IP) scanning for all SAP Hosted Cloud products. WhiteSource usage is mandatory for security vulnerability scanning, in case of certain programming languages
More on supported use-cases on https://go.sap.corp/osssec_tools

getExtensionClassesForScopes.name: licensing-workbench
getExtensionClassesForScopes.description:
To avoid licensing infringement and risks, the corporate Product Standard Licensing enforces the validation and confirmation that all commercial third-party components comprised in your product version (PV) or software component version (SCV) have the appropriate rights for all use and distribution in place. The corporate and mandatory task Commercial 3rd Party & Open Source Validation in Sirius describes how you can prepare the data and request the validation. This task is the successor of the previous âOpen Source Planning and Reportâ and âThird Party Requirementsâ tasks. 
Licensing Workbench is the tool used for these validations.
